Building a Sinatra based application that focuses on dog adoption

1) List out all dependencies for Sinatra to function.
2) Plan the project structure (which controllers feed into which views - White board time!)
3) Figure out what you want your views to Display
4) Stub out the model and controllers and update views as necessary
5) Program

The purpose of this application is for users to be able to sign up and either choose to adopt other pets or put their pet up for adoption.

Sign in page
Create an accounts

Log in
Direct to specific account page (should display information and dogs in your possession)

List a new pet functionality
View and edit any new pet

REQUIREMENTS
+ Build an MVC Sinatra Application.
+ Use ActiveRecord with Sinatra.
+ Use Multiple Models.
+ Use at least one has_many relationship
+ Must have user accounts. The user that created a given piece of content should be the only person who can modify that content
+ You should validate user input to ensure that bad data isn't created
